hat allow for overnight parking. Patapasco station was the original northern terminus of the [[Baltimore and Annapolis Railroad]], which connected to the Curtis Bay Branch of the [[Baltimore and Ohio Railroad]].\n\nBus routes [[Route 14 (MTA Maryland)|14]], [[Route 17 (MTA Maryland)|17]], [[Route 51 (MTA Maryland)|51]], and [[Route 77 (MTA Maryland)|77]] [[lay over]] at the station. [[Route 16 (MTA Maryland)|Route 16]] also passes through the station in both directions along its route.\n\n==Station layout==\n{|table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=3\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" rowspan=6 valign=bottom width=50|'''G'''\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 2px black;border-right:solid 2px black;border-left:solid 2px black;border-top:solid 1px gray;text-align:center;\" colspan=2|<small>[[Side platform]], doors will open on the right</small>\n|-\n|<span style=\"color:#355d82\">'''Southbound'''</span>\n|\u2190 [[Baltimore Light RailLink|<span style=\"color:#355d82\">'''Light Rail'''</span>]] toward {{mtams|BWI Airport}} or {{mtams|Glen Burnie}} <small>({{mtams|Baltimore Highlands}})</small>\n|-\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;\"|<span style=\"color:#355d82\">'''Northbound'''</span>\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;\"|{{0|\u2190}} [[Baltimore Light RailLink|<span style=\"color:#355d82\">'''Light Rail'''</span>]] toward {{mtams|Fairgrounds}} or {{mtams|Hunt Valley}} <small>({{mtams|Cherry Hill}})</small> \u2192\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;border-right:solid 2px black;border-left:solid 2px black;border-top:solid 2px black;text-align:center;\" colspan=2|<small>[[Side platform]], doors will open on the right</small>\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=100|Street level\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=400|Exit/entrance\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080625022925/http://www.mtamaryland.com/services/lightrail/schedule/ Schedules]\